node.text:
Mayweather isn't just a boxer...he's a businessman. He's built a HUGE name for himself leading to an estimated $450M net worth(other networths have been reported for 2021).

His upfront fee for his fight against Paul was said to be $10M. Overall he reported he'll make between $50M and $100M.

This is the difference between him and many athletes...it takes a great businessman to be able to make big pay days like this.

Watch the ful video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r4fcOyfVoLE&t=77s

Follow us @businessequity

node.text:
Money can lead to many options, but working only for money isn't going to bring you happiness. You need to have a bigger end goal.

A rich lifestyle is purely about money whereas a wealthy lifestyle is all about balance. Figure out whats more important to you!

Follow us @businessequity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'DECTER Genevieve Roch-Decter, CFA @GRDecter 1.Risk is fine in moderation. It's alright to make some risky investments here and there, but it shouldn't be a high % of your portfolio. 20% of my portfolio is dedicated to higher-risk investments.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve och-Decter, CFA @GRDecter 2. The best deals are private. Even though there are tons of great options to invest in with the open stock market investing in private deals gives you access to more 10x and 100x opportunities.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 3. Big gains are nice, but consistent gains are key. Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be an image of text that says '-DECTER Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 4. Day trading is bad. This should be self-explanatory, but if Warren Buffet, the greatest investor of all time isn't making any trades, neither am I.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. May be a Twitter screenshot of 1 person and text that says 'DECTER Genevieve Roch-Dector, CFA @GRDecter 5. Most people are better with ETF's. When it comes down to picking individual stocks, most people (even hedge funds) will not outperform basic EFTs like vOO and SPY over 30 years. If you you can't beat them, join them.'.

Photo by Business Equity on August 08, 2021. node.text:
This is a rough break down of how millionaires and billionaires use paintings to avoid taxes.

Credit to: @jaketran.io 
Follow us @businessequity

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Business Equity on August 07, 2021. May be an image of 4 people and text that says 'BusinessEquity THE HARDER YOU WORK THE MORE TAXES You'll pay. The harder your money works, the less taxes you'll pay. This is one of the main reason how Warren Buffett's tax rate is 17 while the average American's rate is 24%'.

node.text:
When your money is working for you you are getting paid in capital gains, dividends, etc...

This is how the rich make money. When you do this your tax rate is far lower because investments and assets are taxed at a lower rate than wages.

This means the average American pays a higher percent of taxes than the average millionaire. This is why we always stress to get money and buy assets!

Follow us @businessequity
